	<!-- <h2></h2> -->
			<div class="longform post_img fullwidth">
			<img src="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2023/09/torsos.jpg" alt="" class="entry_post"/>
		</div>
				<h1>The 17 Best Book Covers of September</h1>
		<h2>The Latest Fall Fashions </h2>
    <div class="inner">
		<div class="post_header_wrapper">
    				</div>
				<div class="author_info" itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
			<div class="author_name">By&nbsp;<a href="https://lithub.com/author/emily-temple/" itemprop="url"><span itemprop="name">Emily&nbsp;Temple</span></a></div>
			<div class="author_hr"><hr/></div>
			<div class="publish_date">September 28, 2023</div>
		</div>
		<div class="social_links">
						<a href="https://twitter.com/intent/tweet?via=lithub&text=The+17+Best+Book+Covers+of+September&url=https%3A%2F%2Flithub.com%2Fthe-17-best-book-covers-of-september%2F"><span class="social_twitter"></span></a>
			<a href="https://www.facebook.com/sharer.php?u=https%3A%2F%2Flithub.com%2Fthe-17-best-book-covers-of-september%2F&t=The+17+Best+Book+Covers+of+September"><span class="social_facebook"></span></a>
					</div>
    <div class="inner">
    	<!-- Begin main content -->
    	<div class="inner_wrapper fullwidth">
    			
										<!-- Begin each blog post -->
						<div class="post_wrapper" style="padding-top:0;">
							<div class="post_inner_wrapper">
						    	<div class="post_wrapper_inner">
										<div class="inner_wrapper fullwidth">
								        
										<p>Another month of books, another month of book covers. We&#8217;ve entered what is arguably the most exciting season for books, and so naturally, the covers follow. Here are my favorites from September:</p>
<span class="caption"><img decoding="async" fetchpriority="high" data-attachment-id="227348" data-permalink="https://lithub.com/the-17-best-book-covers-of-september/61jnjogfrxl-_ac_uf10001000_ql80_/" data-orig-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2023/09/61JnJoGFRxL._AC_UF10001000_QL80_.jpg" data-orig-size="673,1000" data-comments-opened="1" data-image-meta="{&quot;aperture&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;credit&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;camera&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;caption&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;created_timestamp&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;copyright&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;focal_length&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;iso&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;shutter_speed&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;orientation&quot;:&quot;0&quot;}" data-image-title="61JnJoGFRxL._AC_UF1000,1000_QL80_" data-image-description="" data-image-caption="&lt;p&gt;Ida Vitale, tr. Sarah Pollack, &lt;a href=&quot;https://bookshop.org/a/132/9780811231923&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;noopener&quot;&gt;&lt;em&gt;Time Without Keys&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/a&gt;; design by Tyler Comrie (New Directions, September 4)&lt;/p&gt;
" data-medium-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2023/09/61JnJoGFRxL._AC_UF10001000_QL80_-202x300.jpg" data-large-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2023/09/61JnJoGFRxL._AC_UF10001000_QL80_.jpg" class="wp-image-227348" src="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2023/09/61JnJoGFRxL._AC_UF10001000_QL80_.jpg" alt="" width="450" height="669" srcset="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2023/09/61JnJoGFRxL._AC_UF10001000_QL80_.jpg 673w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2023/09/61JnJoGFRxL._AC_UF10001000_QL80_-202x300.jpg 202w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2023/09/61JnJoGFRxL._AC_UF10001000_QL80_-40x60.jpg 40w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2023/09/61JnJoGFRxL._AC_UF10001000_QL80_-34x50.jpg 34w" sizes="(max-width: 450px) 100vw, 450px" /> Ida Vitale, tr. Sarah Pollack, <a href="https://bookshop.org/a/132/9780811231923" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external"><em>Time Without Keys</em></a>; design by Tyler Comrie (New Directions, September 4)</span>
<p>This layered, cut paper treatment is delicate and extravagant at once.</p>
<span class="caption"><img decoding="async" data-attachment-id="227349" data-permalink="https://lithub.com/the-17-best-book-covers-of-september/81-szsrbfl-_ac_uf10001000_ql80_/" data-orig-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2023/09/81-SZsrBFL._AC_UF10001000_QL80_.jpg" data-orig-size="666,1000" data-comments-opened="1" data-image-meta="{&quot;aperture&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;credit&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;camera&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;caption&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;created_timestamp&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;copyright&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;focal_length&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;iso&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;shutter_speed&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;orientation&quot;:&quot;0&quot;}" data-image-title="81-SZsrB+FL._AC_UF1000,1000_QL80_" data-image-description="" data-image-caption="&lt;p&gt;Sean Michaels, &lt;a href=&quot;https://bookshop.org/a/132/9781662602320&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;noopener&quot;&gt;&lt;em&gt;Do You Remember Being Born?&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/a&gt;; cover design by Rodrigo Corral, 3D illustration by Danny Jones (Astra House, September 5)&lt;/p&gt;
" data-medium-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2023/09/81-SZsrBFL._AC_UF10001000_QL80_-200x300.jpg" data-large-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2023/09/81-SZsrBFL._AC_UF10001000_QL80_.jpg" class="wp-image-227349" src="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2023/09/81-SZsrBFL._AC_UF10001000_QL80_.jpg" alt="" width="450" height="676" srcset="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2023/09/81-SZsrBFL._AC_UF10001000_QL80_.jpg 666w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2023/09/81-SZsrBFL._AC_UF10001000_QL80_-200x300.jpg 200w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2023/09/81-SZsrBFL._AC_UF10001000_QL80_-40x60.jpg 40w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2023/09/81-SZsrBFL._AC_UF10001000_QL80_-33x50.jpg 33w" sizes="(max-width: 450px) 100vw, 450px" /> Sean Michaels, <a href="https://bookshop.org/a/132/9781662602320" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external"><em>Do You Remember Being Born?</em></a>; cover design by Rodrigo Corral, 3D illustration by Danny Jones (Astra House, September 5)</span>
<p>What to even say about this glorious, insane book cover? Sometimes, the weirder the better.</p>
<span class="caption"><img decoding="async" data-attachment-id="222515" data-permalink="https://lithub.com/lit-hubs-most-anticipated-books-of-2023-part-two/71nereh394l-_sl1500_/" data-orig-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2023/06/71nEReh394L._SL1500_.jpg" data-orig-size="1000,1500" data-comments-opened="1" data-image-meta="{&quot;aperture&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;credit&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;camera&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;caption&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;created_timestamp&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;copyright&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;focal_length&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;iso&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;shutter_speed&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;orientation&quot;:&quot;0&quot;}" data-image-title="Ariel Dorfman, The Suicide Museum" data-image-description="" data-image-caption="&lt;p&gt;Ariel Dorfman, &lt;a href=&quot;https://bookshop.org/a/132/9781635423891&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;noopener&quot;&gt;&lt;em&gt;The Suicide Museum&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/a&gt;; cover design by TK TK (Other Press, September 5)&lt;/p&gt;
" data-medium-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2023/06/71nEReh394L._SL1500_-200x300.jpg" data-large-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2023/06/71nEReh394L._SL1500_-683x1024.jpg" class="wp-image-222515" src="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2023/06/71nEReh394L._SL1500_-683x1024.jpg" alt="Ariel Dorfman, The Suicide Museum" width="450" height="675" srcset="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2023/06/71nEReh394L._SL1500_-683x1024.jpg 683w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2023/06/71nEReh394L._SL1500_-200x300.jpg 200w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2023/06/71nEReh394L._SL1500_-768x1152.jpg 768w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2023/06/71nEReh394L._SL1500_-40x60.jpg 40w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2023/06/71nEReh394L._SL1500_-33x50.jpg 33w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2023/06/71nEReh394L._SL1500_.jpg 1000w" sizes="(max-width: 450px) 100vw, 450px" /> Ariel Dorfman, <a href="https://bookshop.org/a/132/9781635423891" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external"><em>The Suicide Museum</em></a>; cover design by John Gall Design (Other Press, September 5)</span>
<p>This reminds me pleasantly of those Nabokov backlist butterfly box redesigns (which John Gall art directed—gasp—fourteen years ago), but with a sleekly updated vibe.</p>
<span class="caption"><img decoding="async" loading="lazy" data-attachment-id="227350" data-permalink="https://lithub.com/the-17-best-book-covers-of-september/51spp1iindl-_ac_uf10001000_ql80_/" data-orig-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2023/09/51Spp1iindL._AC_UF10001000_QL80_.jpg" data-orig-size="621,1000" data-comments-opened="1" data-image-meta="{&quot;aperture&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;credit&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;camera&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;caption&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;created_timestamp&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;copyright&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;focal_length&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;iso&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;shutter_speed&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;orientation&quot;:&quot;0&quot;}" data-image-title="51Spp1iindL._AC_UF1000,1000_QL80_" data-image-description="" data-image-caption="&lt;p&gt;Anne Serre, tr. Mark Hutchinson, &lt;a href=&quot;https://bookshop.org/a/132/9780811234511&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;noopener&quot;&gt;&lt;em&gt;A Leopard-Skin Hat&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/a&gt;; cover design by Joan Wong (New Direction, September 5)&lt;/p&gt;
" data-medium-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2023/09/51Spp1iindL._AC_UF10001000_QL80_-186x300.jpg" data-large-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2023/09/51Spp1iindL._AC_UF10001000_QL80_.jpg" class="wp-image-227350" src="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2023/09/51Spp1iindL._AC_UF10001000_QL80_.jpg" alt="" width="450" height="725" srcset="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2023/09/51Spp1iindL._AC_UF10001000_QL80_.jpg 621w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2023/09/51Spp1iindL._AC_UF10001000_QL80_-186x300.jpg 186w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2023/09/51Spp1iindL._AC_UF10001000_QL80_-37x60.jpg 37w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2023/09/51Spp1iindL._AC_UF10001000_QL80_-31x50.jpg 31w" sizes="(max-width: 450px) 100vw, 450px" /> Anne Serre, tr. Mark Hutchinson, <a href="https://bookshop.org/a/132/9780811234511" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external"><em>A Leopard-Skin Hat</em></a>; cover design by Joan Wong (New Direction, September 5)</span>
<p>This is just a really good idea, and plus it made me smile.</p><div class="uAkM9B85" style="clear:both;float:left;width:100%;margin:0 0 20px 0;"><div class="htlad-LH_PP_IC"></div></div>
<span class="caption"><img decoding="async" loading="lazy" data-attachment-id="227351" data-permalink="https://lithub.com/the-17-best-book-covers-of-september/pd/" data-orig-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2023/09/pd.jpg" data-orig-size="940,1500" data-comments-opened="1" data-image-meta="{&quot;aperture&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;credit&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;camera&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;caption&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;created_timestamp&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;copyright&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;focal_length&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;iso&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;shutter_speed&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;orientation&quot;:&quot;0&quot;}" data-image-title="pd" data-image-description="" data-image-caption="&lt;p&gt;Gina Rushton, &lt;a href=&quot;https://bookshop.org/a/132/9781662602382&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;noopener&quot;&gt;&lt;em&gt;The Parenthood Dilemma&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/a&gt;; cover design by Rodrigo Corral, photo by Jason Fulford and Tamara Shopsin (Astra House, September 5)&lt;/p&gt;
" data-medium-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2023/09/pd-188x300.jpg" data-large-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2023/09/pd-642x1024.jpg" class="wp-image-227351" src="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2023/09/pd-642x1024.jpg" alt="" width="450" height="718" srcset="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2023/09/pd-642x1024.jpg 642w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2023/09/pd-188x300.jpg 188w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2023/09/pd-768x1226.jpg 768w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2023/09/pd-38x60.jpg 38w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2023/09/pd-31x50.jpg 31w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2023/09/pd.jpg 940w" sizes="(max-width: 450px) 100vw, 450px" /> Gina Rushton, <a href="https://bookshop.org/a/132/9781662602382" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external"><em>The Parenthood Dilemma</em></a>; cover design by Rodrigo Corral, photo by Jason Fulford and Tamara Shopsin (Astra House, September 5)</span>
<p>I love the strangeness of the image, neatly paired with the cover text.</p>
<span class="caption"><img decoding="async" loading="lazy" data-attachment-id="222509" data-permalink="https://lithub.com/lit-hubs-most-anticipated-books-of-2023-part-two/attachment/9780374606374/" data-orig-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2023/06/9780374606374.jpg" data-orig-size="1650,2531" data-comments-opened="1" data-image-meta="{&quot;aperture&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;credit&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;camera&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;caption&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;created_timestamp&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;copyright&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;focal_length&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;iso&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;shutter_speed&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;orientation&quot;:&quot;0&quot;}" data-image-title="Yiyun Li, Wednesday&#8217;s Child" data-image-description="" data-image-caption="&lt;p&gt;Yiyun Li, &lt;a href=&quot;https://bookshop.org/a/132/9780374606374&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;noopener&quot;&gt;&lt;em&gt;Wednesday&#8217;s Child&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/a&gt;; cover design by Na Kim (FSG, September 5)&lt;/p&gt;
" data-medium-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2023/06/9780374606374-196x300.jpg" data-large-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2023/06/9780374606374-668x1024.jpg" class="wp-image-222509" src="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2023/06/9780374606374-668x1024.jpg" alt="Yiyun Li, Wednesday's Child" width="450" height="690" srcset="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2023/06/9780374606374-668x1024.jpg 668w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2023/06/9780374606374-196x300.jpg 196w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2023/06/9780374606374-768x1178.jpg 768w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2023/06/9780374606374-39x60.jpg 39w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2023/06/9780374606374-1001x1536.jpg 1001w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2023/06/9780374606374-1335x2048.jpg 1335w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2023/06/9780374606374-33x50.jpg 33w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2023/06/9780374606374.jpg 1650w" sizes="(max-width: 450px) 100vw, 450px" /> Yiyun Li, <a href="https://bookshop.org/a/132/9780374606374" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external"><em>Wednesday&#8217;s Child</em></a>; cover design by Na Kim (FSG, September 5)</span>
<p>(In real life, it shimmers.)</p>
<span class="caption"><img decoding="async" loading="lazy" data-attachment-id="227352" data-permalink="https://lithub.com/the-17-best-book-covers-of-september/4dc720a36f412716fa7152de4d78c2580a6b7ed8-1556x2400/" data-orig-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2023/09/4dc720a36f412716fa7152de4d78c2580a6b7ed8-1556x2400-1.jpg" data-orig-size="1556,2400" data-comments-opened="1" data-image-meta="{&quot;aperture&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;credit&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;camera&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;caption&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;created_timestamp&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;copyright&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;focal_length&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;iso&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;shutter_speed&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;orientation&quot;:&quot;0&quot;}" data-image-title="4dc720a36f412716fa7152de4d78c2580a6b7ed8-1556&#215;2400" data-image-description="" data-image-caption="&lt;p&gt;Victor Heringer, tr. James Young, &lt;a href=&quot;https://bookshop.org/a/132/9780811237475&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;noopener&quot;&gt;&lt;em&gt;The Love of Singular Men&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/a&gt;; cover design by Pablo Delcan (New Directions, September 5)&lt;/p&gt;
" data-medium-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2023/09/4dc720a36f412716fa7152de4d78c2580a6b7ed8-1556x2400-1-195x300.jpg" data-large-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2023/09/4dc720a36f412716fa7152de4d78c2580a6b7ed8-1556x2400-1-664x1024.jpg" class="wp-image-227352" src="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2023/09/4dc720a36f412716fa7152de4d78c2580a6b7ed8-1556x2400-1-664x1024.jpg" alt="" width="450" height="694" srcset="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2023/09/4dc720a36f412716fa7152de4d78c2580a6b7ed8-1556x2400-1-664x1024.jpg 664w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2023/09/4dc720a36f412716fa7152de4d78c2580a6b7ed8-1556x2400-1-195x300.jpg 195w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2023/09/4dc720a36f412716fa7152de4d78c2580a6b7ed8-1556x2400-1-768x1185.jpg 768w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2023/09/4dc720a36f412716fa7152de4d78c2580a6b7ed8-1556x2400-1-39x60.jpg 39w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2023/09/4dc720a36f412716fa7152de4d78c2580a6b7ed8-1556x2400-1-996x1536.jpg 996w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2023/09/4dc720a36f412716fa7152de4d78c2580a6b7ed8-1556x2400-1-1328x2048.jpg 1328w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2023/09/4dc720a36f412716fa7152de4d78c2580a6b7ed8-1556x2400-1-32x50.jpg 32w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2023/09/4dc720a36f412716fa7152de4d78c2580a6b7ed8-1556x2400-1.jpg 1556w" sizes="(max-width: 450px) 100vw, 450px" /> Victor Heringer, tr. James Young, <a href="https://bookshop.org/a/132/9780811237475" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external"><em>The Love of Singular Men</em></a>; cover design by Pablo Delcan (New Directions, September 5)</span>
<p>A simple, straightforward text-based cover that&#8217;s elevated by the color choices.</p>
<span class="caption"><img decoding="async" loading="lazy" data-attachment-id="227353" data-permalink="https://lithub.com/the-17-best-book-covers-of-september/9780143137115__66593/" data-orig-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2023/09/9780143137115__66593.jpg" data-orig-size="853,1280" data-comments-opened="1" data-image-meta="{&quot;aperture&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;credit&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;camera&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;caption&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;created_timestamp&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;copyright&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;focal_length&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;iso&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;shutter_speed&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;orientation&quot;:&quot;1&quot;}" data-image-title="9780143137115__66593" data-image-description="" data-image-caption="&lt;p&gt;J. Michael Martinez, &lt;a href=&quot;https://bookshop.org/a/132/9780143137115&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;noopener&quot;&gt;&lt;em&gt;Tarta Americana&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/a&gt;; art direction by Lynn Buckley, art by Amber Cowan (Penguin Books, September 12)&lt;/p&gt;
" data-medium-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2023/09/9780143137115__66593-200x300.jpg" data-large-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2023/09/9780143137115__66593-682x1024.jpg" class="wp-image-227353" src="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2023/09/9780143137115__66593-682x1024.jpg" alt="" width="450" height="675" srcset="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2023/09/9780143137115__66593-682x1024.jpg 682w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2023/09/9780143137115__66593-200x300.jpg 200w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2023/09/9780143137115__66593-768x1152.jpg 768w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2023/09/9780143137115__66593-40x60.jpg 40w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2023/09/9780143137115__66593-33x50.jpg 33w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2023/09/9780143137115__66593.jpg 853w" sizes="(max-width: 450px) 100vw, 450px" /> J. Michael Martinez, <a href="https://bookshop.org/a/132/9780143137115" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external"><em>Tarta Americana</em></a>; art direction by Lynn Buckley, art by Amber Cowan (Penguin Books, September 12)</span>
<p>Another cover that makes excellent use of a piece of art.</p>
<span class="caption"><img decoding="async" loading="lazy" data-attachment-id="227354" data-permalink="https://lithub.com/the-17-best-book-covers-of-september/713ola767ll-_ac_uf10001000_ql80_/" data-orig-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2023/09/713Ola767lL._AC_UF10001000_QL80_.jpg" data-orig-size="647,1000" data-comments-opened="1" data-image-meta="{&quot;aperture&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;credit&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;camera&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;caption&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;created_timestamp&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;copyright&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;focal_length&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;iso&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;shutter_speed&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;orientation&quot;:&quot;0&quot;}" data-image-title="713Ola767lL._AC_UF1000,1000_QL80_" data-image-description="" data-image-caption="&lt;p&gt;Laura Picklesimer, &lt;a href=&quot;https://bookshop.org/a/132/9781951213893&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;noopener&quot;&gt;&lt;em&gt;Kill for Love&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/a&gt;; cover design by Jaya Nicely (Unnamed Press, September 12)&lt;/p&gt;
" data-medium-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2023/09/713Ola767lL._AC_UF10001000_QL80_-194x300.jpg" data-large-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2023/09/713Ola767lL._AC_UF10001000_QL80_.jpg" class="wp-image-227354" src="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2023/09/713Ola767lL._AC_UF10001000_QL80_.jpg" alt="" width="450" height="696" srcset="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2023/09/713Ola767lL._AC_UF10001000_QL80_.jpg 647w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2023/09/713Ola767lL._AC_UF10001000_QL80_-194x300.jpg 194w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2023/09/713Ola767lL._AC_UF10001000_QL80_-39x60.jpg 39w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2023/09/713Ola767lL._AC_UF10001000_QL80_-32x50.jpg 32w" sizes="(max-width: 450px) 100vw, 450px" /> Laura Picklesimer, <a href="https://bookshop.org/a/132/9781951213893" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external"><em>Kill for Love</em></a>; cover design by Jaya Nicely (Unnamed Press, September 12)</span>
<p>A parade of pink torsos? Gotta love it.</p><div class="D2nbBIMt" style="clear:both;float:left;width:100%;margin:0 0 20px 0;"><div class="htlad-LH_PP_IC"></div></div>
<span class="caption"><img decoding="async" loading="lazy" data-attachment-id="227355" data-permalink="https://lithub.com/the-17-best-book-covers-of-september/61tetoyqaol-_ac_uf10001000_ql80_/" data-orig-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2023/09/61TetOyQAoL._AC_UF10001000_QL80_.jpg" data-orig-size="625,1000" data-comments-opened="1" data-image-meta="{&quot;aperture&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;credit&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;camera&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;caption&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;created_timestamp&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;copyright&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;focal_length&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;iso&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;shutter_speed&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;orientation&quot;:&quot;0&quot;}" data-image-title="Soula Emmanuel, &lt;a href=&quot;https://bookshop.org/a/132/9781558610132&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;noopener&quot;&gt;&lt;em&gt;Wild Geese&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/a&gt;; cover design by Dana Li (Feminist Press, September 12)" data-image-description="" data-image-caption="&lt;p&gt;Soula Emmanuel, &lt;a href=&quot;https://bookshop.org/a/132/9781558610132&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;noopener&quot;&gt;&lt;em&gt;Wild Geese&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/a&gt;; cover design by Dana Li (Feminist Press, September 12)&lt;/p&gt;
