<p>Another layered cover (in a shade of green you don&#8217;t see too often on book covers).</p>
<span class="caption"><img decoding="async" loading="lazy" data-attachment-id="227356" data-permalink="https://lithub.com/the-17-best-book-covers-of-september/91w4gkjhqjl-_ac_uf10001000_ql80_/" data-orig-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2023/09/91w4GkjhQjL._AC_UF10001000_QL80_.jpg" data-orig-size="663,1000" data-comments-opened="1" data-image-meta="{&quot;aperture&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;credit&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;camera&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;caption&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;created_timestamp&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;copyright&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;focal_length&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;iso&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;shutter_speed&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;orientation&quot;:&quot;0&quot;}" data-image-title="Julius Taranto, &lt;em&gt;&lt;a class=&quot;external&quot; href=&quot;https://bookshop.org/a/132/9780316513074&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;noopener&quot;&gt;How I Won a Nobel Prize&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/em&gt;; cover design by TK TK (Little Brown, September 12)" data-image-description="" data-image-caption="&lt;p&gt;Julius Taranto, &lt;em&gt;&lt;a class=&quot;external&quot; href=&quot;https://bookshop.org/a/132/9780316513074&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;noopener&quot;&gt;How I Won a Nobel Prize&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/em&gt;; cover design by TK TK (Little Brown, September 12)&lt;/p&gt;
" data-medium-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2023/09/91w4GkjhQjL._AC_UF10001000_QL80_-199x300.jpg" data-large-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2023/09/91w4GkjhQjL._AC_UF10001000_QL80_.jpg" class="wp-image-227356" src="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2023/09/91w4GkjhQjL._AC_UF10001000_QL80_.jpg" alt="Julius Taranto, &lt;em&gt;&lt;a class=&quot;external&quot; href=&quot;https://bookshop.org/a/132/9780316513074&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;noopener&quot;&gt;How I Won a Nobel Prize&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/em&gt;; cover design by TK TK (Little Brown, September 12) " width="450" height="679" srcset="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2023/09/91w4GkjhQjL._AC_UF10001000_QL80_.jpg 663w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2023/09/91w4GkjhQjL._AC_UF10001000_QL80_-199x300.jpg 199w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2023/09/91w4GkjhQjL._AC_UF10001000_QL80_-40x60.jpg 40w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2023/09/91w4GkjhQjL._AC_UF10001000_QL80_-33x50.jpg 33w" sizes="(max-width: 450px) 100vw, 450px" /> Julius Taranto, <em><a class="external" href="https://bookshop.org/a/132/9780316513074" target="_blank" rel="noopener">How I Won a Nobel Prize</a></em>; cover design by Lucy Kim (Little Brown, September 12)</span>
<p>Now <em>this </em>one reminds me pleasantly of Peter Mendlesund&#8217;s Kafka backlist redesigns (only 12 years ago, whew). The coin makes for a very fun twist.</p>
<div class="mceTemp"></div>
<span class="caption"><img decoding="async" loading="lazy" data-attachment-id="227358" data-permalink="https://lithub.com/the-17-best-book-covers-of-september/81klucpc5bl-_ac_uf10001000_ql80_/" data-orig-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2023/09/81KlUcpc5bL._AC_UF10001000_QL80_.jpg" data-orig-size="647,1000" data-comments-opened="1" data-image-meta="{&quot;aperture&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;credit&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;camera&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;caption&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;created_timestamp&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;copyright&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;focal_length&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;iso&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;shutter_speed&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;orientation&quot;:&quot;0&quot;}" data-image-title="Anya Johanna DeNiro, &lt;a href=&quot;https://bookshop.org/a/132/9781618732088&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;noopener&quot;&gt;&lt;em&gt;Okpsyche&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/a&gt;; cover image: “Psyche Asleep in a Landscape,” by Karl Joseph Aloys Agricola, 1837 (Small Beer Press, September 12)" data-image-description="" data-image-caption="&lt;p&gt;Anya Johanna DeNiro, &lt;a href=&quot;https://bookshop.org/a/132/9781618732088&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;noopener&quot;&gt;&lt;em&gt;Okpsyche&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/a&gt;; cover image: “Psyche Asleep in a Landscape,” by Karl Joseph Aloys Agricola, 1837 (Small Beer Press, September 12)&lt;/p&gt;
" data-medium-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2023/09/81KlUcpc5bL._AC_UF10001000_QL80_-194x300.jpg" data-large-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2023/09/81KlUcpc5bL._AC_UF10001000_QL80_.jpg" class="wp-image-227358" src="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2023/09/81KlUcpc5bL._AC_UF10001000_QL80_.jpg" alt="Anya Johanna DeNiro, &lt;a href=&quot;https://bookshop.org/a/132/9781618732088&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;noopener&quot;&gt;&lt;em&gt;Okpsyche&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/a&gt;; cover image: “Psyche Asleep in a Landscape,” by Karl Joseph Aloys Agricola, 1837 (Small Beer Press, September 12) " width="450" height="696" srcset="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2023/09/81KlUcpc5bL._AC_UF10001000_QL80_.jpg 647w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2023/09/81KlUcpc5bL._AC_UF10001000_QL80_-194x300.jpg 194w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2023/09/81KlUcpc5bL._AC_UF10001000_QL80_-39x60.jpg 39w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2023/09/81KlUcpc5bL._AC_UF10001000_QL80_-32x50.jpg 32w" sizes="(max-width: 450px) 100vw, 450px" /> Anya Johanna DeNiro, <a href="https://bookshop.org/a/132/9781618732088" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external"><em>Okpsyche</em></a>; cover image: “Psyche Asleep in a Landscape,” by Karl Joseph Aloys Agricola, 1837 (Small Beer Press, September 12)</span>
<p>It takes a few moments to see the subtle shifting in the painting, but what&#8217;s really daring is that bleeding text treatment.</p>
<span class="caption"><img decoding="async" loading="lazy" data-attachment-id="222528" data-permalink="https://lithub.com/lit-hubs-most-anticipated-books-of-2023-part-two/71z6ksuxpol-_ac_uf10001000_ql80_/" data-orig-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2023/06/71z6KsuxpoL._AC_UF10001000_QL80_.jpg" data-orig-size="671,1000" data-comments-opened="1" data-image-meta="{&quot;aperture&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;credit&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;camera&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;caption&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;created_timestamp&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;copyright&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;focal_length&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;iso&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;shutter_speed&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;orientation&quot;:&quot;0&quot;}" data-image-title="Nathan Hill, Wellness" data-image-description="" data-image-caption="&lt;p&gt;Nathan Hill, &lt;a href=&quot;https://bookshop.org/a/132/9780593536117&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;noopener&quot;&gt;&lt;em&gt;Wellness&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/a&gt;; cover design by Oliver Munday (Knopf, September 19)&lt;/p&gt;
" data-medium-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2023/06/71z6KsuxpoL._AC_UF10001000_QL80_-201x300.jpg" data-large-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2023/06/71z6KsuxpoL._AC_UF10001000_QL80_.jpg" class="wp-image-222528" src="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2023/06/71z6KsuxpoL._AC_UF10001000_QL80_.jpg" alt="Nathan Hill, Wellness" width="450" height="671" srcset="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2023/06/71z6KsuxpoL._AC_UF10001000_QL80_.jpg 671w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2023/06/71z6KsuxpoL._AC_UF10001000_QL80_-201x300.jpg 201w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2023/06/71z6KsuxpoL._AC_UF10001000_QL80_-40x60.jpg 40w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2023/06/71z6KsuxpoL._AC_UF10001000_QL80_-34x50.jpg 34w" sizes="(max-width: 450px) 100vw, 450px" /> Nathan Hill, <a href="https://bookshop.org/a/132/9780593536117" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external"><em>Wellness</em></a>; cover design by Oliver Munday (Knopf, September 19)</span>
<p>Big and bold and beautiful.</p>
<span class="caption"><img decoding="async" loading="lazy" data-attachment-id="218241" data-permalink="https://lithub.com/see-the-cover-for-daniel-masons-north-woods/attachment/9780593597033/" data-orig-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/9780593597033-scaled.jpg" data-orig-size="1719,2560" data-comments-opened="1" data-image-meta="{&quot;aperture&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;credit&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;camera&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;caption&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;created_timestamp&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;copyright&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;focal_length&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;iso&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;shutter_speed&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;orientation&quot;:&quot;0&quot;}" data-image-title="daniel mason north woods" data-image-description="" data-image-caption="&lt;p&gt;Daniel Mason, &lt;em&gt;&lt;a class=&quot;external&quot; href=&quot;https://bookshop.org/a/132/9780593597033&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;noopener&quot;&gt;North Woods&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/em&gt;; cover design by Anna Kochman (Random House, September 19)&lt;/p&gt;
" data-medium-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/9780593597033-201x300.jpg" data-large-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/9780593597033-687x1024.jpg" class="wp-image-218241" src="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/9780593597033-687x1024.jpg" alt="daniel mason north woods" width="450" height="670" srcset="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/9780593597033-687x1024.jpg 687w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/9780593597033-201x300.jpg 201w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/9780593597033-768x1144.jpg 768w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/9780593597033-40x60.jpg 40w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/9780593597033-1031x1536.jpg 1031w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/9780593597033-1375x2048.jpg 1375w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/9780593597033-34x50.jpg 34w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/9780593597033-scaled.jpg 1719w" sizes="(max-width: 450px) 100vw, 450px" /> Daniel Mason, <em><a class="external" href="https://bookshop.org/a/132/9780593597033" target="_blank" rel="noopener">North Woods</a></em>; cover design by Anna Kochman (Random House, September 19)</span>
<p>“There was so much imagery to be inspired by in this book, it was hard to zero in one thing!” <a href="https://lithub.com/see-the-cover-for-daniel-masons-north-woods/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Anna Kochman told Lit Hub</a>. “Originally this illustration was part of a panel design, using a few different images, but it was the one that seemed to call to everyone. I think the style of illustration and the amazing expression in the eyes of the catamount really suit the tone of the book, and when we let it stand alone it felt right.” It certainly does.</p><div class="V15okxAv" style="clear:both;float:left;width:100%;margin:0 0 20px 0;"><div class="htlad-LH_PP_IC"></div></div>
<span class="caption"><img decoding="async" loading="lazy" data-attachment-id="227359" data-permalink="https://lithub.com/the-17-best-book-covers-of-september/9781646052790_fc_1024x10242x-copy/" data-orig-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2023/09/9781646052790_FC_1024x1024@2x-copy.jpg" data-orig-size="450,696" data-comments-opened="1" data-image-meta="{&quot;aperture&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;credit&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;camera&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;caption&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;created_timestamp&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;copyright&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;focal_length&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;iso&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;shutter_speed&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;orientation&quot;:&quot;1&quot;}" data-image-title="Luis Felipe Fabre, tr. Heather Cleary, &lt;em&gt;&lt;a class=&quot;external&quot; href=&quot;https://bookshop.org/a/132/9781646052790&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;noopener&quot;&gt;Recital of the Dark Verses&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/em&gt;; cover design by Alban Fischer (Deep Vellum, September 19)" data-image-description="" data-image-caption="&lt;p&gt;Luis Felipe Fabre, tr. Heather Cleary, &lt;em&gt;&lt;a class=&quot;external&quot; href=&quot;https://bookshop.org/a/132/9781646052790&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;noopener&quot;&gt;Recital of the Dark Verses&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/em&gt;; cover design by Alban Fischer (Deep Vellum, September 19)&lt;/p&gt;
" data-medium-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2023/09/9781646052790_FC_1024x1024@2x-copy-194x300.jpg" data-large-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2023/09/9781646052790_FC_1024x1024@2x-copy.jpg" class="size-full wp-image-227359" src="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2023/09/9781646052790_FC_1024x1024@2x-copy.jpg" alt="Luis Felipe Fabre, tr. Heather Cleary, &lt;em&gt;&lt;a class=&quot;external&quot; href=&quot;https://bookshop.org/a/132/9781646052790&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;noopener&quot;&gt;Recital of the Dark Verses&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/em&gt;; cover design by Alban Fischer (Deep Vellum, September 19) " width="450" height="696" srcset="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2023/09/9781646052790_FC_1024x1024@2x-copy.jpg 450w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2023/09/9781646052790_FC_1024x1024@2x-copy-194x300.jpg 194w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2023/09/9781646052790_FC_1024x1024@2x-copy-39x60.jpg 39w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2023/09/9781646052790_FC_1024x1024@2x-copy-32x50.jpg 32w" sizes="(max-width: 450px) 100vw, 450px" /> Luis Felipe Fabre, tr. Heather Cleary, <em><a class="external" href="https://bookshop.org/a/132/9781646052790" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Recital of the Dark Verses</a></em>; cover design by Alban Fischer (Deep Vellum, September 19)</span>
<p>Macabre and brilliant.</p>
<span class="caption"><img decoding="async" loading="lazy" data-attachment-id="222683" data-permalink="https://lithub.com/lit-hubs-most-anticipated-books-of-2023-part-two/91yax8motl-_sl1500_/" data-orig-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2023/06/91YaX8MotL._SL1500_.jpg" data-orig-size="987,1500" data-comments-opened="1" data-image-meta="{&quot;aperture&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;credit&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;camera&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;caption&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;created_timestamp&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;copyright&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;focal_length&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;iso&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;shutter_speed&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;orientation&quot;:&quot;0&quot;}" data-image-title="the wolves of eternity knausgaard" data-image-description="" data-image-caption="&lt;p&gt;Karl Ove Knausgaard, tr. Martin Aitkin, &lt;em&gt;&lt;a class=&quot;external&quot; href=&quot;https://bookshop.org/a/132/9780593490839&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;noopener&quot;&gt;The Wolves of Eternity&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/em&gt;; cover design by Stephanie Ross (Penguin, September 19)&lt;/p&gt;
" data-medium-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2023/06/91YaX8MotL._SL1500_-197x300.jpg" data-large-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2023/06/91YaX8MotL._SL1500_-674x1024.jpg" class="wp-image-222683" src="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2023/06/91YaX8MotL._SL1500_-674x1024.jpg" alt="the wolves of eternity knausgaard" width="450" height="684" srcset="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2023/06/91YaX8MotL._SL1500_-674x1024.jpg 674w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2023/06/91YaX8MotL._SL1500_-197x300.jpg 197w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2023/06/91YaX8MotL._SL1500_-768x1167.jpg 768w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2023/06/91YaX8MotL._SL1500_-39x60.jpg 39w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2023/06/91YaX8MotL._SL1500_-33x50.jpg 33w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2023/06/91YaX8MotL._SL1500_.jpg 987w" sizes="(max-width: 450px) 100vw, 450px" /> Karl Ove Knausgaard, tr. Martin Aitkin, <em><a class="external" href="https://bookshop.org/a/132/9780593490839" target="_blank" rel="noopener">The Wolves of Eternity</a></em>; cover design by Stephanie Ross (Penguin, September 19)</span>
<p>This looks like a simple cover at first glance, but it&#8217;s actually playing with perspective in some really interesting ways—look for the sky behind the text, the light in the corners. Where are we?</p>
<span class="caption"><img decoding="async" loading="lazy" data-attachment-id="222531" data-permalink="https://lithub.com/lit-hubs-most-anticipated-books-of-2023-part-two/51msbtw-pfl-_ac_uf10001000_ql80_/" data-orig-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2023/06/51MsbtW-pfL._AC_UF10001000_QL80_.jpg" data-orig-size="664,1000" data-comments-opened="1" data-image-meta="{&quot;aperture&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;credit&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;camera&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;caption&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;created_timestamp&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;copyright&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;focal_length&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;iso&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;shutter_speed&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;orientation&quot;:&quot;0&quot;}" data-image-title="Vauhini Vara, This is Salvaged: Stories" data-image-description="" data-image-caption="&lt;p&gt;Vauhini Vara, &lt;a href=&quot;https://bookshop.org/a/132/9780393541731&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;noopener&quot;&gt;&lt;em&gt;This is Salvaged&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/a&gt;; cover design by TK TK (W.W. Norton, September 26)&lt;/p&gt;
" data-medium-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2023/06/51MsbtW-pfL._AC_UF10001000_QL80_-199x300.jpg" data-large-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2023/06/51MsbtW-pfL._AC_UF10001000_QL80_.jpg" class="wp-image-222531" src="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2023/06/51MsbtW-pfL._AC_UF10001000_QL80_.jpg" alt="Vauhini Vara, This is Salvaged: Stories" width="450" height="678" srcset="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2023/06/51MsbtW-pfL._AC_UF10001000_QL80_.jpg 664w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2023/06/51MsbtW-pfL._AC_UF10001000_QL80_-199x300.jpg 199w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2023/06/51MsbtW-pfL._AC_UF10001000_QL80_-40x60.jpg 40w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2023/06/51MsbtW-pfL._AC_UF10001000_QL80_-33x50.jpg 33w" sizes="(max-width: 450px) 100vw, 450px" /> Vauhini Vara, <a href="https://bookshop.org/a/132/9780393541731" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external"><em>This is Salvaged</em></a>; cover design by Keith Hayes, art direction by Steve Attardo (W.W. Norton, September 26)</span>
<p>Behold the power of a single, dynamic image (and the text treatment to support it).</p>
										
																				
																		
										<div class="post_wrapper author">
											<div id="about_the_author">
												<div class="gravatar"><a href="https://lithub.com/author/emily-temple/"><img src="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2019/11/Emily-Temple_select_9612_NS1sm-100x100.jpg" width="100" height="100" alt="Emily Temple" class="avatar avatar-100 wp-user-avatar wp-user-avatar-100 alignnone photo" /></a></div>
												<div class="description author withsidebar">
													<h6><a href="https://lithub.com/author/emily-temple/">Emily Temple</a></h6>
													Emily Temple is the managing editor at Lit Hub. Her first novel, <em>The Lightness</em>, was published by William Morrow/HarperCollins in June 2020. <a href="https://bookshop.org/a/317/9780062905338" rel="noopener noreferrer" target="_blank" class="external">You can buy it here.</a>																										<div class="website">
						    							<i class="fa fa-link"></i>
